3.By using AngularJS We Can Create
  Reusable Components By using

    1.Custom Directives

    2.Custom Services

    3.Custom Filters



4.AngularJS is a Open Source

    We Can Customize the Framework Accroding to Application Requirement.

5.By using AngularJS We Can Develop Single Page Applications.

6.AngularJS Reduces the Burden on the Server

  by implementing the Business

  components client side by using MVC.


7. Angular Applications are

  Cross Browser Compatable Applications.


Disadvantages Of AngularJS
-
1.Secuirity.

2.Client Should Enable the JavaScript

  then only angular applications will execute.

3.No Coding Standards in AngularJS ,

  so Undestanding the Angular Applications Are Difficult.



GitHub.

    - GitHub is the Repository.

    - GitHub is the Open Source.

    - All the Developers Collabratively Connect

      to GitHub while Working with the Project.

GitHub Operations.

1.Creating the Repository.

2.Add the Files to the Repository.

3.Save the Changes in files / Commit the Files.

4.Branching in GitHub.

5.Merge in GitHub.

6.Integrating the GitHub to the IDE'S

        WebStrom

        Visual Studio

        Ecilipse

7.Push the Code to the Remote Repository.

8.Pull the Code from the Remote Repository.

9.Merge Conflicts


Creating the Repository (Locally).


Step 1.

    Download and Install the GIT

    WebSite: https://git-scm.com/downloads

    file name : Git-2.12.1-64-bit.exe



    Create the Folder in any Drive.

    Ex.
            ------------------------------
      d:\githubdemo.

          rigth click on the githubdemo --->

                            select Git Bash Here -->

                                        $git init.

              ------------------------------


     set user credentials to the GitHub.

     $git config --global user.name "XXX"

     $git config --global user.email "XXXXXXX"


2.Add the files to the Repository.

$ touch index.html


3.Commit the files to repository.

$git add index.html

$git commit

Press i

Type : initial commit

Press Esc

Type :wq

Press Enter



From Second Commit Onwards follow the Below Git Commands.


$git add .

$git commit -m "Message"


Creating the Branch.

$ git branch my_branch

$ git checkout my_branch


Merging the Branches.

$git merge my_branch


